result.name: Twelve Flavors

reviews.text: If you like spicy Chinese food, you will like this. Taste is delicious and quite authentic. The lunch menu has variety of famous spicy dishes, in very affordable price. Will definitely visit there again.

The fish in sour and spicy soup with flavors of preserved vegetables is very outstanding, almost 10 out of 10, especially with the great bargain of only $218 or 248 for such a generous portion which could be shared among 4 people. Definitely add the special kind of thick and chewy vermicelli to this dish, you'll like it! The 麻香鍋 was nicely done as well. Chicken cartilage is particularly good. The spices made the pot very tasty, good to go with rice too. The dessert 紅糖糍粑 is so yummy, crunchy outside, soft and chewy inside, it's glutinous. We liked it a lot! A very nice resto specialized in spicy dish and fish in sour and spicy soup, resembling the hottest restaurants in China. Stood out well from the street with lots of red lanterns hung up outside the shop, interiors made u feel like going back to China too.

Yum! The dry hotpot is especially great. Service was good, with most staff able to speak English. We were allowed to BYOB before, but their liquor licence has now been granted. Lots of good vegetarian/vegan options, easily found on the menu. The place has too much single-use plastic - a lot of drinks come in sealed plastic cups which you need a straw to drink from.

Very low key but also overall very delicious. You pick your own ingredients and then it's cooked and served in a "communal style pot", kept warm by the pots mass. 

Main negative is that it's perhaps a bit too low market, asking you to pay 2 Hong Kong dollars for a napkin and mostly serving warm water out of a dinky plastic jug.

Would recommend a visit.

Not very honest. Was given wrong change, but the shop wouldn’t admit it, and didn’t apologize. And instead of finding my check (which is still on top of the pile of the paper) they choose to take care of all the other guests, making it more difficult to find my check and verify if what I said is true. At the end they gave my money back, but the way they dealt with this incident makes me feel they deliberately did so.
